  "texts": [
    "Other contributing factors of scientific thinking include prior knowledge, memory, data generated from experiments, accidental events, and systematically generated evidence 20.",
    "Figure 1 shows a conceptual framework of scientific thinking, its supporting and necessary cognitive capacities and attributes, and their primary relationships.",
    "As shown in Figure 1, the focus of our study is a small subset of hypothesis generation, which is a subset of scientific thinking.",
    "Data-Driven Hypothesis Generation in Clinical Research",
    "Scientific thinking has the potential to exert a substantial impact on scientific education and scientific discoveries."
